@jbarik I found out what's causing this. You just need to install the cssmodule_ls server, I'm myself using Mason for that. Then you need to pass some specific server settings so it doesn't conflict with 'Go to definition' from the tsserver.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3494708/232250853-58d71c9d-f49f-4920-aed2-a21429861cdc.png)

So this doesn't have to do with native Neovim LSP.

Here's my config[^*]:

[^*]: Do the same thing if your using just lspconfig.

```lua
require('mason-lspconfig').setup_handlers({
  function(server_name)
    lspconfig[server_name].setup({
      on_attach = on_attach,
      capabilities = capabilities,
      settings = {
        Lua = {
          diagnostics = { globals = { 'vim' } },
        },
        -- NOTE: For some reason, stylelint isn't loading my config file with 
        -- rules for avoiding false positives when using PostCss plugins.
        css = {
          validate = true,
          lint = {
            unknownAtRules = 'ignore',
          },
        },
        cssmodules = { -- <= This is what you need, don't forget to install the server
          capabilities = {
            definitionProvider = false
          }
        }
      },
    })
  end,
})
```

Source: https://github.com/antonk52/cssmodules-language-server#configuration

I hope it helps...

